body:
`$strobe` doesn't always interact correctly with timing (#3363). Test:
```systemverilog
module t(input clk);
   event e1;
   event e2;
   int v = 0;

   initial begin
     #1 $strobe("v = %0d", v); ->e1;
     @e2 $strobe("v = %0d", v); ->e1;
     @e2 $strobe("v = %0d", v); ->e1;
     @e2 $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
     $finish;
   end

   initial begin
     @e1 v = 1; #1 ->e2;
     @e1 v = 2; #1 ->e2;
     @e1 v = 3; #1 ->e2;
   end
endmodule
```
Verilator output:
```
v = 0
v = 1
v = 2
*-* All Finished *-*
- t/t_timing_strobe.v:21: Verilog $finish
```
Desired output:
```
v = 1
v = 2
v = 3
*-* All Finished *-*
- t/t_timing_strobe.v:21: Verilog $finish
```
Issue is, the `$strobe` gets executed too early, in `act`. That's before the process waiting on `e1` gets resumed.

[Zip with test case](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/files/9383387/t_timing_strobe.zip)
